## Step-by-Step Guide to Install Sass

### You need Node.js and npm installed.

- node -v, npm -v, If not installed, download and install from: https://nodejs.org/

### Step 2: Install Sass via npm

- npm install -D sass or a specific version: npm install sass@3.7.4

### Step 3: Add Sass Files

- Create a .scss file (e.g., styles.scss)

### Compile Sass to CSS

- Use the following command: npx sass styles.scss styles.css

### To Watch for Changes Automatically:

- npx sass --watch styles.scss styles.css

### To watch a whole folder

- npx sass --watch scss/:css/

### (Optional): Add a Script to package.json

"scripts": {
"sass": "sass --watch scss:css"
} With this you can run: npm run sass

#### Final project structure

my-project/
│
├── scss/
│ └── styles.scss
├── css/
│ └── styles.css
├── index.html
├── package.json
